==English==
===Etymology===
from Spanish ''[[tocar]]'', cognate with ''[[touch]]''

===Pronunciation===
*tōk, /təʊk/, /<tt>t@Uk</tt>/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-əʊk|Rhymes: -əʊk]]

===Noun===
'''toke''' ([[tokes]])

# (''slang'') A puff of marijuana.
#: ''The painter took a thoughtful toke off the [[joint]], then passed it along.''
# (''US casino slang'') A gratuity.
#: ''I gave the maitre d’ a $10 toke and he just laughed.''

===Intransitive verb===
'''to toke'''

# (''slang'') To smoke marijuana.
#: ''You can't just expect to toke your way through life.''

===Transitive verb===
# (''US casino slang'') To give a gratuity to.
#: ''You have to toke the maitre d’ at least $50 if you want a really good table.''